NOMFUNDO Mtshali hated keeping secrets . . . But her confession to her boyfriend, that she was pregnant by another man, may have led to her death!The 18-year-old died on Tuesday after being stabbed nine times, allegedly by the boyfriend.He was found hanging from a tree in Ntabamhlophe near Nsuze, northern KZN. Nomfundo&rsquo;s uncle, Jabulani Mgobhozi (66), said the boyfriend should just have hanged himself and spared her life. &ldquo;My niece was still in grade 11 at Khethimfundo High School. She had a bright future ahead of her, but this jealous man killed her. He should have died alone,&rdquo; he said. Nomfundo, who was three months pregnant, had wanted to live an honest life. &ldquo;That was why she told the boyfriend the truth about the baby not being his,&rdquo; he said. &ldquo;He came to our house on Tuesday night, greeted the family and left before saying he would be back.&ldquo;A few minutes later, we noticed Nomfundo wasn&rsquo;t home. While we were still wondering where she was, we heard a scream. My two sons and I rushed to help her.&rdquo;As they were running towards the scene, the screaming stopped. When they arrived Nomfundo was already dead. They saw the boyfriend running into the bushes. &ldquo;I called the police and they confirmed she was dead after being stabbed,&rdquo; he said. He said he heard the next day that the boyfriend had hanged himself. KZN police spokeswoman Captain Nqobile Gwala said Nsuze cops had opened an inquest docket and a murder case. &ldquo;The woman was allegedly stabbed to death by a 25-year-old man who was found hanging the next day,&rdquo; she said.